songs.title: The End
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Do you see me?
I'm lost in a world I call home
And I’m bleedin'
I've been wastin’ away on hold
Speechless, all the words I know don't affect at all
How I need this
Losing grip on [?] onto all
I need a friend

[Pre-Chorus]
I'm not ready to give up
I'm still givin' all I've got

[Chorus]
You know I've seen the end
I've seen the end and it’s far too close
If we make amends
If we make amends we’ll also fill the laws
Will it cause me hurt?
Chances are I'll find my way back home
But I’ve seen the end
I've seen the end and it's far too close

[Verse 2]
Oh I'm sleepless
On my thoughts I’ve lost control
I'm not faithless
I'm just tired of the way I hold
I'm near the end

[Pre-Chorus]
I'm not ready to give up
I'm still givin' all I've got

[Chorus]
You know I've seen the end
I've seen the end and it's far too close
If we make amends
If we make amends we'll also fill the laws
Will it cause me hurt?
Chances are I'll find my way back home
But I've seen the end
I've seen the end and it's far too close

[Bridge]
How it's tasteless
The rotation of the feelings I know
Am I [?] to find the strength not to fall?

[Chorus]
You know I've seen the end
I've seen the end and it's far too close
If we make amends
If we make amends we'll also fill the laws
Will it cause me hurt?
Chances are I'll find my way back home
But I've seen the end
I've seen the end and it's far too close
